OL,3,CIndustry warns proposed gambling tax
OL,4,Crises would cost up to 40,000 jobs
OL,6,FBetting firms are warning that
OL,7,Fproposed tax increases on the
OL,8,Findustry, backed by Gordon Brown,
OL,9,Fwould "devastate jobs, undermine the
OL,10,Feconomy and drive billions into the
OL,11,Fhands of the gambling black market."
OL,13,FThe Betting and Gaming Council (BGC)
OL,14,Fcommissioned EY - a firm specialising
OL,15,Fin economic modelling that advises
OL,16,Fcompanies and governments on tax - to
OL,17,Fanalyse the impact of a set of
OL,18,Fproposals published earlier this year
OL,19,Fby the Institute for Public Policy
OL,20,FResearch (IPPR), a think tank.
