OL,6,FGordon Brown gave his support to the
OL,7,Fchanges, arguing the money should be
OL,8,Fused to remove the cap that currently
OL,9,Fonly allows families to claim benefits
OL,10,Ffor their first two children.
OL,12,FBut EY concludes the proposed tax
OL,13,Fincreases would not raise anything
OL,14,Flike the sums the IPPR assumes and
OL,15,Fwould have profoundly negative
OL,16,Funintended consequences.
