OL,3,CIndustry warns proposed gambling tax
OL,4,Crises would cost up to 40,000 jobs
OL,6,FEY says the government might see just
OL,7,Fover #1 billion in extra tax in the
OL,8,Fshort term but when factors such as
OL,9,Fjob losses, lower corporation and
OL,10,FNational Insurance contributions, and
OL,11,Fclosed betting shops are taken into
OL,12,Faccount, the real gain for the
OL,13,FTreasury could drop to less than #500
OL,14,Fmillion.
OL,16,FGrainne Hurst, chief executive of the
OL,17,FBGC, said: "It is now clear these
OL,18,Ffurther tax rises are a direct threat
OL,19,Fto British jobs and economic growth."
