OL,3,CIndustry warns proposed gambling tax
OL,4,Crises would cost up to 40,000 jobs
OL,6,FThe statement added: "Tax raids like
OL,7,Fthose proposed would mean fewer
OL,8,Fbetting shops, casinos, and bingo
OL,9,Fhalls, fewer jobs, and a huge boost to
OL,10,Fthe growing, unsafe gambling black
OL,11,Fmarket, while not raising anywhere
OL,12,Fnear the tax claimed."
OL,14,FEY identifies three major flaws in the
OL,15,FIPPR report:
OL,17,F1. It assumes gamblers would continue
OL,18,Fto spend the same even if betting
OL,19,Fcompanies worsen the odds.
